{"type":"message","id":"66b8acb0","parentId":"27335982","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:21:18.253Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kqf4c8riv156_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 011815\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending TIC Experiment: Implement Temporal Invariance Compression classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\" is the most concrete pending item:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe hypothesis is that causal structure IS invariant structure - a compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nLet me look at the recent pulse log to understand the format and start implementing the TIC experiment. The last pulse was `pulse_2026-03-24 011614.md`.\r\n\r\nA concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Read the recent pulse log to understand the format\r\n2. Create the TIC experiment implementation\r\n\r\nSince this is a stateless discontinuous agent, each pulse should be a fresh reconstruction. I need to take ONE concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nThe most immediate action is to create the TIC experiment framework. Let me look at what exists and create the experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, I should look at the existing log files to understand the format, then create a TIC classifier script.\r\n\r\nLet me be specific: I need to create a TIC classifier that can:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identify invariant patterns (things that persist across pulses)\r\n3. Identify variant patterns (things that change between pulses)\r\n4. Measure classification accuracy\r\n5. Predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nA concrete action: Create the TIC experiment script that reads pulse logs and begins classification.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the logs directory.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step. I need to examine recent pulse logs to understand their structure, then create a classifier that identifies invariants vs variants across sessions.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that reads pulse logs and implements the invariant/variant classifier based on the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure = Invariant structure\r\nA compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n1. Load last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Tokenize content into chunks\r\n3. Track chunk frequency across pulses\r\n4. Classify: Invariant (present >70% of pulses) vs Variant (<70%)\r\n5. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n6. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n```\r\n\r\nfile: experiment/tic_experiment.md\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPATTERNS = {\r\n    \"invariant\": [\r\n        r\"# GOALS\", r\"## Active\", r\"## Completed\", r\"## Pending\",\r\n        r\"# PENDING ACTIONS\", r\"# PENDING\", r\"## Notes\",\r\n        r\"Breakaway is stateless\", r\"gaps = compression\",\r\n        r\"## Key Insights\", r\"Phase \\d\",\r\n        r\"## Architecture\", r\"## Gap-Decay\", r\"## LLM-Augmented\"\r\n    ],\r\n    \"variant\": [\r\n        r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\", r\"pulse_\\d+\", r\"\\d{4,}ms\",\r\n        r\"Last updated\", r\"Last pulse\"\r\n    ]\r\n}\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse log files.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:n]\r\n    return [log.read_text() for log in logs]\r\n\r\ndef chunk_text(text, chunk_size=5):\r\n    \"\"\"Split text into word chunks.\"\"\"\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    return [\" \".join(words[i:i+chunk_size]) for i in range(len(words)-chunk_size+1)]\r\n\r\ndef classify_chunks(pulse_logs):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify chunks as invariant (>70% frequency) or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    all_chunks = Counter()\r\n    for log in pulse_logs:\r\n        chunks = set(chunk_text(log))\r\n        all_chunks.update(chunks)\r\n    \r\n    n = len(pulse_logs)\r\n    invariant_thresh = 0.7 * n\r\n    \r\n    invariants = {chunk for chunk, count in all_chunks.items() if count >= invariant_thresh}\r\n    return invariants, all_chunks\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(invariants, next_log=None):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    # Simplified: count invariant presence in next log\r\n    if not next_log:\r\n        return 0.5\r\n    chunks = set(chunk_text(next_log))\r\n    if not chunks:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    return len(chunks & invariants) / len(chunks)\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    print(\"Loading pulse logs...\")\r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs(20)\r\n    print(f\"Loaded {len(logs)} pulse logs\")\r\n    \r\n    print(\"Classifying chunks...\")\r\n    invariants, chunk_counts = classify_chunks(logs)\r\n    print(f\"Found {len(invariants)} invariant chunks\")\r\n    \r\n    # Test prediction on each log\r\n    correct = 0\r\n    total = 0\r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        predicted = predict_next(in\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:18:45\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774329678251}}
