{"type":"message","id":"3be5d5dc","parentId":"daa697e3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:21:34.234Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hjlkdvaodi85_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 012015\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiment/tic_experiment.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. There's a pending TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that causal discovery and compression are the same problem.\r\n\r\nFor the next pulse, I should:\r\n1. Implement the TIC classifier as outlined\r\n2. This advances Phase 1 by testing the hypothesis\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action that advances this goal. I should implement the TIC classifier on the pulse log files.\r\n\r\nLooking at what's available:\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` files exist\r\n- I need to implement invariant/variant classification\r\n- Test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create the TIC experiment script/code that can:\r\n1. Parse pulse logs\r\n2. Classify content as invariant (persisting across sessions) vs variant (session-specific)\r\n3. Measure accuracy\r\n4. Attempt next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. The pulse logs are available but no classifier exists yet to test invariant/variant classification.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that will analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns, classify content, and measure prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"Phase \\d\",  # Phases persist\r\n    r\"Goals:\",    # Goal structure persists\r\n    r\"PENDING\",   # Pending items persist\r\n    r\"research/\", # Research files persist\r\n    r\"architecture\",  # Core concepts persist\r\n]\r\n\r\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",  # Dates vary\r\n    r\"pulse_\\d{8}\",        # Pulse IDs vary\r\n    r\"Now:\",               # Timestamps vary\r\n    r\"Last updated:\",      # Update times vary\r\n]\r\n\r\ndef extract_content(log_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract meaningful content from pulse log, removing timestamps/metadata.\"\"\"\r\n    content = log_path.read_text()\r\n    # Remove frontmatter-like headers\r\n    content = re.sub(r'#+\\s*Pulse \\d+.*?\\n', '', content)\r\n    content = re.sub(r'Date:.*?\\n', '', content)\r\n    content = re.sub(r'Status:.*?\\n', '', content)\r\n    return content\r\n\r\ndef classify_sentence(sentence, invariant_count, variant_count):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify a sentence as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    inv_hits = sum(1 for p in INVARIANT_PATTERNS if re.search(p, sentence, re.I))\r\n    var_hits = sum(1 for p in VARIANT_PATTERNS if re.search(p, sentence))\r\n    if inv_hits > var_hits:\r\n        return \"invariant\"\r\n    elif var_hits > inv_hits:\r\n        return \"variant\"\r\n    return \"neutral\"\r\n\r\ndef analyze_invariants(logs):\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze which content persists across sessions.\"\"\"\r\n    all_invariants = Counter()\r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        content = extract_content(log)\r\n        for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n            matches = re.findall(pattern, content, re.I)\r\n            all_invariants.update(matches)\r\n    return all_invariants\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(previous_logs, current_log):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict what should appear in next pulse based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    invariants = analyze_invariants(previous_logs)\r\n    current_content = extract_content(current_log)\r\n    \r\n    predicted = []\r\n    for item, count in invariants.most_common(10):\r\n        if count >= len(previous_logs) * 0.7:  # Appears in 70%+ of logs\r\n            if item.lower() not in current_content.lower():\r\n                predicted.append(item)\r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    logs = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[-20:]  # Last 20 logs\r\n    if len(logs) < 5:\r\n        print(f\"Need at least 5 logs, found {len(logs)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Analyzing {len(logs)} pulse logs...\")\r\n    \r\n    # Classification accuracy\r\n    classifications = {\"invariant\": 0, \"variant\": 0, \"neutral\": 0}\r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        content = extract_content(log)\r\n        sentences = content.split('.')\r\n        for sent in sentences:\r\n            cls = classify_sentence(sent.strip(), 0, 0)\r\n            classifications[cls] += 1\r\n    \r\n    total_classified = classifications[\"invariant\"] + classifications[\"variant\"]\r\n    if total_classified > 0:\r\n        inv_pct = classifications[\"invariant\"] / total_classified * 100\r\n        print(f\"Classification: {inv_pct:.1f}% invariant (target: >70%)\")\r\n    \r\n    # Prediction accuracy\r\n    correct_predictions = 0\r\n    total_predictions = 0\r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        predicted = predict_next_pulse(logs[:i\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:20:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774329694232}}
